  "term": "thm:limit-sum",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Sum Rule for Function Limits",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $f,g:A\\to\\mathbb{R}$ and let $c$ be a cluster point of $A$. If\n$\\lim_{x\\to c}f(x)=L$ and $\\lim_{x\\to c}g(x)=M$, then\n\\[\n \\lim_{x\\to c}(f+g)(x)=L+M.\n\\]",
